episodes.title: Rumble on the Wonder Wheel
episodes.plot: Midge returns with a new game plan after getting kicked off Shy Baldwin's tour. Joel is too successful for his own good. Susie finds a creative way to get the cash she needs.

episodes.title: Billy Jones and the Orgy Lamps
episodes.plot: Midge has Abe and Rose over for dinner. Shirley tries to find Joel a new wife. An unexpected cab ride leads to new opportunities.

episodes.title: Everything Is Bellmore
episodes.plot: Midge runs into an old friend at work. Susie finds out she has a close friend. Abe's job gets personal. Rose's matchmaking business draws attention.

episodes.title: Interesting People on Christopher Street
episodes.plot: Midge establishes new rules. Susie gets a leg up from old friends. Abe has more in common with Asher than he thought.

episodes.title: How to Chew Quietly and Influence People
episodes.plot: Susie hones her managerial style. Rose's professional skills land her an incredible opportunity. Midge and Susie take advantage of some high society perks.

episodes.title: Maisel vs. Lennon: The Cut Contest
episodes.plot: Word of Midge's act is spreading. Imogene gets a new job and a new name. Sophie just wants to help.

episodes.title: Ethan... Esther... Chaim
episodes.plot: Abe forgets his tobacco. Joel raises a glass with Moishe. Midge learns firsthand about America's bicameral system of legislature.

episodes.title: How Do You Get to Carnegie Hall?
episodes.plot: Midge and Joel debate Greek mythology. Susie finds a second phone line. A blizzard brings unexpected consequences.
